# Tailor Book — Mobile app environment
#
# This file is a TEMPLATE — copy it to `.env` and adjust for your environment.
# Variables prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ are inlined into the bundle at build time.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOCAL SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set this to your PC's LAN IP address so the API server (port 4000) is
# reachable from the mobile app regardless of platform.
#
# 1. Find your LAN IP (Windows):   ipconfig | findstr "IPv4"
# 2. Find your LAN IP (Mac/Linux): ifconfig | grep "inet "
# 3. Replace 192.168.0.89 below with your IP.
#
# WHY LOCALHOST DOES NOT WORK:
#   - iOS Simulator:          localhost → your Mac (works only if server is on Mac)
#   - Android Emulator:       localhost → the emulator itself (NEVER works)
#   - Physical device:        localhost → the phone itself (NEVER works)
#   - Android Web (your PC):  localhost → your PC (works)
#
# The auto-detect logic in utils/api.ts will handle:
#   - Web on the same PC:      same hostname, port 4000
#   - iOS Simulator on Mac:    localhost:4000
#   - Android Emulator:        NOT covered by auto-detect → needs LAN IP here
#   - Physical device on LAN:  LAN IP from this file
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Replace with your actual LAN IP, then copy this file to `.env`
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://YOUR_LAN_IP_HERE:4000
